Friendly relationship between kindergartens of DPRK and China established 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 10 (KCNA) -- A ceremony for establishing friendly relationship between the Pyongyang Okryu Kindergarten no. 2 and the Yanji City June 1 Kindergarten of China was held at the Pyongyang Okryu Kindergarten no. 2 yesterday.
 Present at the ceremony were members of the c.c., the DPRK-China Friendship Association, officials concerned and its employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were members of the good-will delegation of the Yanji city, China, People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries led by its vice-president Cui Yongjun, employees of the Yanji City June 1 Kindergarten and a staff member of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony speeches on establishing the friendly relationship were made. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the participants looked round the kindergarten and enjoyed an art performance given by children.

Indian group for study of self-reliance formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 10 (KCNA) -- The Indian group for study of self-reliance was inaugurated with due ceremony in New Delhi on Oct. 3.
 Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, said at the ceremony that the Juche idea was so creditably applied to reality that the DPRK has turned into a country strong in independence in the international arena and the man-centered social system has been established in the DPRK for the first time in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editor of the newspaper Krishna Ebota was elected chairman of the group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to leader Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

Invincible WPK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 10 (KCNA) -- The Korean people are now celebrating the 56th anniversary of the foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea (October 10, 1945), their guiding force.
 On this day the Korean people look back with deep emotion upon the proud road of struggle covered by the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 56 years have passed since the WPK proclaimed its foundation but it is 75 years since the formation of the down-with-imperialism union at which the party began to take its root. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK has developed into a seasoned veteran party in the arduous revolutionary struggle and construction work and the fierce struggle against the imperialists and all enemies. It has also grown to be an invincible revolutionary party which enjoys absolute support and trust from the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The party has opened up a new way for the popular masses' cause of independence, the socialist cause, and made brilliant victories and tremendous changes in this course, thus performing immortal feats to be recorded in the history forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The party has been able to create an example of revolutionary party building and attain the great successes in the revolution and construction because it has become a party of the leader and formed the single-hearted unity with the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic cause of developing the WPK into the eternal party of President Kim Il Sung has been successfully realized by leader Kim Jong Il. So, it can preserve its character as the revolutionary party of Juche type forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has been highly praised and respected by the people as an outstanding leader of the WPK and the revolution from his early years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nearly 40 years of his revolutionary activities are the immortal history in which he has created a model of present politics.

Leader of Thai Democratic Party on Korean issue 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 10 (KCNA) -- Chuan Leekpai, leader of the Thai Democratic Party, met the DPRK ambassador to Thailand on Oct. 4 on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 He said that the world fully recognizes that President Kim Il Sung, founder of the WPK, made great contributions to the Korean revolution and the development of the world politics in his lifetime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il has made tireless efforts for the well-being and prosperity of the Korean people and the world revolution. he is an experienced politician who deals well with political relations with different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I am pleased that the friendly relations between Thailand and the DPRK have developed on good terms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 North-South Joint Declaration is of weighty significance in reunifying Korea and ensuring peace and stability on the Korean peninsula and the Korean issue should be solved according to it.

Swedish charge d'affaires ad interim hosts reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 10 (KCNA) -- Swedish charge d'affaires ad interim here hosted a reception at the embassy yesterday on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Invited were Ji Jae Ryong, vice department director of the central committee of the WPK, Choe Su Hon, vice foreign minister, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Diplomatic envoys of Germany and Great Britain were also invited. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Homage paid to President Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 10 (KCNA) -- Senior party and state officials, commanding officers of the Korean People's Army, servicemen of its three services, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters and people from all walks of life today visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 A floral basket was placed before the statue of the president in the joint name of the WPK Central Committee, the Central Military Commission of the WPK, the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After paying respectful homage to the statue of the president, they bowed in most profound reverence to him who lies in state for perpetuity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round orders and medals awarded to him by foreign countries, the portrait of him with a sunny smile on his face and bronze relievos in the mourner's hall and the train he used during his on-site guidance and foreign visits and the car he used in the last period of his life.
